And you wonder why I think y'all are wack jobs. 🙄

@KLR50737839 @TMFloresSB @SPStandLeague @KatLaRue7 That's rich. We've been insulted by a stream of paranoid obessives for the crime of asking for a link for a reputable source to the accusation the Scientologists faked the hurricane relief in the Bahamas. It's no wonder I've had an FU attitude as I've been insulted from the start

@KLR50737839 @SPStandLeague @KatLaRue7 @TMFloresSB Oh? You disagree with my use of citation or link to reputable sources reporting fraud by the Church in hurricane relief in the Bahamas?

Do tell.
@TackstonSandra @TMFloresSB @KatLaRue7 @TonyOrtega94 Oh? Does it specifically address hurricane relief in the Bahamas by the "Church?"

@TMFloresSB @KatLaRue7 I simply asked for links to reputable sources for the assertion that Scientology Bahamas hurricane relief was fraudulent. I'm still waiting. I would have more respect if it was just simply admitted that it was speculation based on previous Scientology behavior rather than...this.
@JimHawk67327371 Only a few days?  You can keep it as long as you want.  We're still in hurricane season it might get replaced.

@SPStandLeague @KatLaRue7 I like facts. That's how I was trained and educated. If there's proof they didn't do hurricane relief then fine. I'm ok with that. But it's not too much to ask to see if you're making the accusation. I don't believe them out of hand either. Certainly not from a press release.

@randomname7700 @KatLaRue7 @TroMcManus Why should I? I didn't make a definitive statement that they have sent down hurricane relief. 

Asked a simple question of your compadre who stated they faked it. Did she have links/citations to reporting that proved that? A simple no would have sufficed but, no, here we are. 🙄
